<h1 class="entry-title" style="text-align: center"><b>San Fran artist paints mural of Greta Thunberg using spray said to be 'notorious' for causing global warming</b></h1>



<div class="td-module-meta-info">
<div class="td-post-author-name"><div class="td-author-by">By</div> <a href="">GIANCARLO SOPO</a><div class="td-author-line"> ---------- </div> </div>                   
<span class="td-post-date"><time class="entry-date updated td-module-date" datetime="2020-11-27T09:56:03+00:00">
    OCT. 15, 2017 </time></span>                                                        </div>

</header><br>

</div>

<div class="td-post-sharing-top"></div>

<div class="td-post-content">

<div class="td-post-featured-image"><a href="https://dogstodaymagazine.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Roxi-parcel-dog-copyright-Vets-Now-1-scaled-e1606470770170.jpg" data-caption="" class="td-modal-image"></a></div>
<div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
    The city of San Francisco can now add another problem to its growing list of issues: Environmental waste from a mural of climate activist Greta Thunberg. </div>
    <div style="text-align:left;line-height:19px;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 45);font-size:17px;font-family:acumin-pro-semi-condensed, ' arial', ' sans-serif;';font-weight:700;">Special: </span>
        <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://www.theblaze.com/newsletters/theblaze-textlink" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;word-break:break-word;font-family:acumin-pro-semi-condensed, ' arial', ' sans-serif;';font-weight:700;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);font-size:17px;text-decoration:none;border-width: medium medium 0px; border-style: none; padding: 0px 2px; ">
        Ditch the fake news ==&gt; Click here to get news you can trust sent right to your inbox. It's free! </a></div>
        <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
            <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://www.chron.com/news/science/article/Greta-Thunberg-mural-being-painted-in-San-14821267.php" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">According to the Associated Press</a>, Argentine artist Andres Iglesias, also known by his pseudonym Cobre, has painted a giant mural of the 16-year-old Nobel Peace Prize nominee in Union Square. Iglesias
            <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://sfist.com/2019/11/08/teen-climate-activist-greta-thunberg-gets-huge-mural-in-downtown-sf/" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">told KPIX-TV</a>
            he created the mural because he wants people "to realize [we] have to do something for the world. Otherwise, it's going to be the beginning of our extinction." </div>
            <h3 style="text-align:left;font-family:acumin-pro-semi-condensed, arial, sans-serif;letter-spacing:-0.5px;line-height:1.17em;">'Asthma-inducing'</h3>
            <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
                However, as a video of the project shows, Iglesias is using aerosol spray paint cans for the Thunberg mural, which environmentalists say emit volatile organic compounds that contribute to global warming. </div>
                <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
                    While it is unclear how many spray cans Iglesias has used, the mural spans four stories and at least one smaller project <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://streetsonart.com/it-took-500-cans-of-spray-paint-to-create-this-magnificent-madonna-mural/" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">utilized 500 cans</a>
                    of the paint scientists say can generate asthma-inducing smog. To create the mural of the teenage climate activist, the artist used a respirator that is said to protect painters subjected to noxious fumes. </div>
                    <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
                        As reported in <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/are-aerosols-still-bad/" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">Scientific American</a>, although most aerosol products sold in the U.S. now use propellants, such as compressed gasses and hydrocarbons that "do not deplete the ozone layer," the use of spray cans like the one being used in the Greta Thunberg mural remain harmful to the environment.
                        <br style="text-align:left;">
                        </div>
                        <blockquote style="text-align:left;font-size:19px;line-height:30px;font-family:utopia-std;font-style:italic;color:rgb(143, 143, 143);margin: 1em 40px; ">
                            They still contain hydrocarbons and/or compressed gases notorious for their contribution to global warming. Every time you hit the button, then, you are raising your carbon footprint, albeit ever so slightly. </blockquote>
                            <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
                                Meanwhile, an article in <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/what-effects-do-aerosol-cans-have-on-the-environment.html" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">World Atlas notes</a>
                                that even the cans themselves contribute to pollution and climate change: </div>
                                <div style="margin-top:19px;margin-bottom:19px;text-align:left;">
                                    Thunberg famously <a href="https://archive.md/o/vQRnl/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2019/sep/23/greta-thunberg-to-world-leaders-how-dare-you-you-have-stolen-my-dreams-and-my-childhood-video" target="_blank" style="text-align:left;border-bottom-color:rgb(255, 0, 45);text-decoration:none;color:rgb(42, 42, 42);border-width: medium medium 2px; border-style: none none solid; padding: 0px 2px; ">blasted world leaders</a>
                                    at the United Nations Climate Summit in September: "We are in the beginning of a mass extinction and all you can talk about is money and fairy tales of eternal economic growth â€” how dare you!" Adding, "You have stolen my dreams and my childhood with your empty words." </div>
</div>


